description.en: Time of departure.
Day offset if the day of departure time of the Service Journey differs from the current Operating Day.

The connection between two consecutive Scheduled Stop Points in a Service Journey Link. Each Service Journey Link has a particular departure and arrival time. Service Journey Links allow Routeplanners to calculate shortest Routes more easily since a Journey is executed at a specific time (on a specific Day Type).
The Line.
Indicates if the Link is for boarding.
Indicates if the Link is for alighting.
Time when the Link departs.

A Stop Place represents a station, stop, port, airport or any physical point of access to the transport network.
Each Point inJourney Pattern specifies the visit of a Service to a specific Scheduled Stop Point in a particular order within the pattern.
Nature of use of stop. Default is "access".

The PassingTimes that are the result of the scheduling process and to be published in a timetable are called TimeTabledPassingTimes. 

The TimeTabledPassingTimes are normally generated a long time before the day of operation and are valid over a long period of time (e.g. summer, winter timetable)

usage.en: If same day, zero.

description.en: Provides the specification of codes assigned to particular Vehicle Journeys when operated by Trains of Compound Trains according to a functional purpose (passenger information, operation follow-up, etc.).
An alternative optimised representation of an Operating Period that uses a string of bits to indicate to which days with the period a specific DayType applies.
String of bits (built of "0" and "1"), one for each day in the period: whether valid or not valid on the day.

usage.en: Normally there will be a bit for every day between start and end date. If bit is missing, assume available.

description.en: Days of week to which correspond the (up to first seven) bits.

A VehicleJourney is the defined movement of a vehicle using a specified Journey Pattern on a particular Route. By virtue of being defined for a Day Type, a Vehicle Journey is a class of journeys that would take place at the same time on each day of a specified Day Type.

Day Type on which the Vehicle Journey is worked.
Transport submode of the Journey.
Part of the Vehicle Journey.

Journey Pattern used to make the Vehicle Journey.
Time of departure.

A number of people organized into a community or other social, commercial, or political structure. The group has a common purpose or raison d'être that transcends its individual members and it can act as an agent. An organization often has a hierarchical structure.
